FBIS3-37344 "drsov032_u_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-032 Document Type:Daily Report 16 Feb 1994 Latvia Latvia's Role in `Partnership for Peace' Program LD1502185994 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1700 GMT 15 Feb 94 LD1502185994 Riga Radio Riga Network Language: Latvian Article Type:BFN [Text] Latvian Prime Minister Birkavs told journalists today that Latvia will actively--dependent on financial possibilities-- start cooperating within the framework of the NATO Partnership for Peace program. Birkavs comments came following his return from Brussels. On Monday in Brussels, Birkavs confirmed with his signature Latvia's agreement to the new NATO program. Latvia will initially participate in the formation of a Baltic peacekeeping battalion, arranging its military structures so they correspond with NATO standards. Moreover, Latvia will try to use all the information received from the NATO, as well as taking part in NATO exercises and various educational seminars.
